message_content: Morning Thanks for getting in touch and sorry for the late reply Over the last few months we have been tightening our guest profile criteria There is really three lenses for review which a guest and their company must meet 1. Does it roll up to the UN Sustainable Development Goals 2. Are they introducing system level change into their chosen area? 2. Is there a specific, bold innovation that underpins how they are doing this A great example would be amber electric ( https://www.shapethesystem.org/episodes/dan-adams-co-ceo-co-founder-of-amber-electric ) 1. Rolls up to energy, sustainable, environmental 2. They have created an alternative model for retail energy where customers get access to wholesale energy prices, meaning they can use the cheap, plentiful renewable¬†energy when its available and curtail energy usage 3. They introduced a combination of smart meters and app to enable real time monitoring of the volatile energy prices and device management which would automatically turn off high energy devices such as pool pumps or car charging at peak prices (and on at low prices) The innovation doesn't have to be technology it could regulatory, behavioural, business model .. as long as it's a key to the system they are rethinking If it is super strong in all 3 this is ideal, but if the innovation is not that strong or we aren't seeing it as introducing system level change then we may decline it on this basis. So with this revised more narrow criteria unfortunately this won't be a fit for the show. We previously had a specialist format where we interviewed people operating in the space more broadly in specific verticals (marketing, pr, strategy, comms etc etc) but it didn't land that well so we went back to our core format above Thanks for your understanding Vincent ·êß
